arts.ttl: Newport County 1-3 Gillingham: Ainsworth's side move to the top of League Two as dominant start continues
arts.sum: There was, in fact, one change to the visitors bench, as former Newport player Seb Palmer-Houlden, who made 34 appearances and scored seven goals for the Rodney Parade side, made his return after overcoming a hamstring injury and came on after 72 minutes. Hughes' side then had an opportunity minutes later to double their lead, and it came after referee Leigh Doughty pointed to the penalty spot after Cameron Antwi was brought down.
